Mr Jean Marie-Koffi of the Port of Abidjan, Cote d’Ivoire, yesterday, in Lagos, took over as the new Secretary-General of Ports Management Association of West and Central Africa (PMAWCA), promising to foster better ties among its 22 member nations. Koffi, at a brief handing over ceremony held at the association’s Headquarters in Lagos said that no one nation can achieve seamless port operations without understanding the emerging trend in the sector. The new Secretary General who promised to consolidate on the gains of his predecessor, Augustin Fatondji of Benin Republic noted that, PMAWCA is an example of a regional co-operation which would help member nations to share information that would help grow the region economy. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY FELA! heads to Lagos Airlines closure is choking passengers UN assists rape victims, pregnant IDPs